Archiargiolestes parvulus is a species of Australian damselfly in the family Megapodagrionidae,
commonly known as a midget flatwing. 
It is endemic to south-western Australia, where it inhabits streams, bogs and swamps.Archiargiolestes parvulus is a small damselfly, black metallic in colour with pale markings. It rests with its wings outspread.